      "name": "Bench-scale hemolysis validation against FDA pump experimental data",
      "description": "CFD-predicted hemolysis index compared against published FDA generic centrifugal pump experimental measurements at five flow-speed operating points. Relative hemolysis index RH < 1 satisfied at all points. The UQ campaign (Latin hypercube sampling, n=200, covering ±10% inlet flow, ±5% rotational speed, ±8% viscosity) confirmed model outputs remain within acceptance bounds across the full uncertainty envelope. Sensitivity rankings from the UQ campaign placed rotational speed as the dominant driver of hemolysis variability, consistent with physical expectations.",
